Rating: 4
These beets are so delicious, and so colorful and beautiful - especially lovely with holiday meals. The pre-roasting and peeling step is a bit labor intensive, but well worth the effort. You can make earlier in the day and re-heat in the microwave before serving without any loss in looks or flavor. It is surprising how much wine is used, but in the end result the wine is not predominant - just lovely aromatic deep red beets. Every time I make these beets I am asked for the recipe. It is really a winner.

Rating: 4
Even better than harvard beets. A great pairing with the menu. Yum!! Will make again and again.

Rating: 4
Not only do beets add beautiful color to the plate, but this dish is also very tasty. Cooked as is - be sure to include the leeks because it really makes the dish - and served alongside grilled lamb and "Sauteed Carrots with Rosemary and Lemon." Only difference is that I used (cheap) on-hand merlot. It was a great, fulfilling, and no-carb meal. Loved it.

