Rating: 4
Yum! The wine and leeks reduce to a wonderful, carmely glaze. I used cabernet as that's always open in my house. I found that the beets got too black uncovered at such a high temp, so I covered them with foil half-way through and lowered to 350. Since they still had to simmer 15 min. on the stove, this worked well and they didn't get too mushy. This will be a definite repeat at our table.

Rating: 3
I love beets and thought the recipe was tasty, but many steps. Not sure I would take the time again, but would recommend as the flavor was nice.